paragraph.content:
a person charged before the District Court with any offence may be granted
                    legal aid under these rules for the preparation and conduct of his defence and
                    for any plea arising from the charge sheet; (L.N. 70 of 1973; L.N. 64 of 1978)

is committed for trial
                    for
                    a specified offence;

